Text.SourceString: How lovely to see a new face around here!//You can call me <NPCName>Betty</>, dear.
You’re the first visitor we’ve had in a while.//After the oil spill last year, tourists hardly come anymore.
Remember to reuse what you can and recycle what you can’t, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Right, we don’t have any community recycling machines yet.//<portrait=normal>But all in good time.
Did you know turtles often eat trash? They think it’s plankton or floating seaweed. But they can’t digest it.//<portrait=sad>Eating trash really harms animals.
Do you know that turtles often eat trash? They think it’s plankton or floating seaweed. But they can’t digest it.//<portrait=sad>Eating trash really harms animals.
For old folks like me, Monday is just another day.
I don’t mind refilling the bird feeders around town.//I have a lot of time on my hands.
<NpcName>Pablo</> helps me fix the broken bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>He and his brother are very handy.
This island has a lot of potential.//It’s nice that people are starting to recognize that.
After all, you moved here, didn’t you?
If you have any fruit trees on your farm, don’t chop them down at the end of the season.//Unlike crops that die at the end of the season, they’ll be ready to produce again in the coming year.
Hmm…//You seem preoccupied, dear.
I still bake, just not as much as I used to.//<portrait=concerned>I just don’t have the same energy…
<NpcName>Eva</> and I have a lot in common. We both love red velvet cake.//<portrait=normal>But who doesn’t?
She’s such a ray of sunshine.
<PlayerName>$player</>?
Hmm… Are you all right?
It’s best to use reusable containers, but when you can’t, remember to try to recycle them, yes?
<PlayerName>$player</>?
…Hmm…//You seem preoccupied, dear.
The kids run the Tavern on their own.//It may look easy, but running a food business is a lot of work.
I don’t bother them anymore.//I think they’ve got the Tavern handled.
I talk about a lot of things at school.//<portrait=normal>How to recycle properly, for instance.//It may seem simple, but I want the kids to learn the right way early on.
We can only hope it’ll stick with them into adulthood.
I still bake, just not as much as I used to.//<portrait=concerned>I just don’t have the same energy…
Are you eating enough?
My only advice to you is to keep cooking.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Frank</> is always on the lookout for new recipes to try.
I miss the old days sometimes, don’t you?
Can’t answer that one?//Maybe your old days are different to the ones I remember.
Planting bee-friendly flowers on your farm can help boost the bee population.//If you could build some bee houses too, that would be even better.
<NpcName>Noah</> says I spoil the cats…//<portrait=happy>I’m starting to think he might have a point… Heh heh.
You may want to save some of your harvest.//Put something away for later seasons.
Oh, I don’t know. Maybe for cooking? Just a little tip, dear.
Hmm… I’m going to try to make a batch of popiah sometime this week.
I wonder how many carrots we have left in the fridge.
Kids are very perceptive.//They watch everything we do and mimic our actions.//As adults, we must be careful not to set a bad example.
Yesterday, I taught about all the different things that damage coral reefs and how to prevent them from dying.
I do it every week.//<portrait=normal>I usually volunteer my time at the school, just like my daughter-in-law, <NpcName>Erika</>.
It’s our responsibility to take care of the planet for future generations.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t you agree?
Hmm… I’m going to try to make a batch of popiah sometime this week.
I wonder how many carrots we have left in the fridge?
I know we have some eggplants, but you can’t use eggplants to make popiah.//<portrait=annoyed>It won’t be popiah without carrots.
<NpcName>Noah</> needs to be more careful putting dishes away.//We almost lost a stack of cups the other day when he crammed the cabinet too full.
I like a lot of things about this town.//<portrait=happy>The lake, the wildlife, <NpcName>Jim’s</> smoked salmon… Heh heh.
Make sure to wash your produce with running water before eating it raw, <PlayerName>$player</>.
It’s hygienic to clean our food.//We don’t want to eat dirt.
Be careful of crows. They may seem harmless, but they like to steal crops.
If you’re worried, I hear scarecrows can be effective.
A community garden reminds me of the old days, when we used to share everything we had.
My great-grandparents were part of the farming community on this island. They planted while others fished or built.
Peonies are blooming this time of year.
Will you be planting any at your farm?//<portrait=normal>It’s not too late, you know.
I’ll be bringing red velvet cake tomorrow. I suspect there won’t be many desserts.
I was talking about the Cherry Blossom Festival. What were you talking about, <PlayerName>$player</>?
There’s a calendar in front of the community center that shows festivals and birthdays.//<portrait=normal>Take a look. It’s very handy.
Is something the matter, dear?
I’m planting flowers to help the bee population.//In time, I hope we’ll see more bee houses on the island.
Am I really going to complain about the heat?//<portrait=annoyed>No. I will not.
It is warm…//But warm is good.//<portrait=normal>We need warmth sometimes, yes?//<portrait=annoyed>The humidity, though… Hmm…
It’s too hot for tulips.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I’ll plant irises instead.
My son <NpcName>Frank</> said you also adopted a new pet.
Ah, I’ve already asked you about that, haven’t I? As much as I’d like to, I can’t blame it on old age… I’ve always been this way. Heh heh.
Forgetfulness has become a part of my identity lately. Heh heh.
Sunflowers are blooming this time of year.
Will you be planting any at your farm?
I can’t be outside in the heat for too long. The heat can be…a bit much.
I never get tired of the Fall breeze.//Ah… This is my favorite time of year.
Keep some lotuses in your pantry, <PlayerName>$player</>. You never know when you’ll have a craving for mooncakes.
Raising four children is not easy. Especially when they’re so close in age. It was chaos from the first, but I wouldn’t change it for the world.
I sometimes wish <NpcName>Frank</> would give me some grandchildren! But I respect their decision.
You’re right. There’s always Peanut and Butter. Heh heh. Ah, you made an old lady’s day, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Mooncakes aren’t hard to make. You need lotus, though. Mix it with flour and egg and blend it all together. Try it sometime!
The weather keeps getting colder. It’s not agreeing with my joints.
Oh dear.
*coughs*
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
Your boots are soaking, dear…//Would you please wipe them off at the door?
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
You should go home and rest, dear…//With this weather, you don’t want to catch a cold.
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
Would you wipe your boots at the door, please?
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this…
Is it snowing out?
The kids must be out building snowmen by the park.//<portrait=normal>It used to be the favorite spot for all my kids when it snowed. Heh heh.
The snow is giving me cold feet…
I have to wear extra socks at night.
What a lovely day!//<portrait=happy>I might bake mooncakes later to enjoy with some evening tea.
Why, of course I can bake mooncakes.//I don’t just bake cookies, dear…
Please watch your step. I would hate for you to crush these flowers.
Are you heading to the beach?
<NpcName>Millie</> is the only one who’s building a house in this area… I wonder why it isn’t more popular.
I’ve been trying to get <NpcName>Frank</> to eat more yogurt.//He’s been eating pancakes all the time lately, and <NpcName>Erika</> doesn’t seem to pay much attention to their diet at home.
He and <NpcName>Noah</> are picky when it comes to yogurt.//<portrait=sad>No matter what I put in it, they don’t seem to like it.
I suppose I can’t blame them.//They’re still young, and they think they’ll be healthy forever.//<portrait=normal>But we need to take care of our bodies so our bodies take care of us, yes?
I’m enjoying the view.//<portrait=normal>I was foraging in the woodland earlier, and I think I gathered enough for dinner.
If you feel comfortable in the forest, the area around <NpcName>Kira’s</> cabin is very lush.//<portrait=normal>My late husband used to find plenty of things there.
Have you gone diving lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I must be extra careful walking around here.//One fall and I could break my hip.
Hmm…
I spent a lot of time here at the beach with my late husband.//I don’t care much for money.//Quality time with family is what leaves the deepest imprint in our hearts.
We used to watch the sunsets right there by the tree.//My sons are around your age, and I always tell them to remember to live.//<portrait=happy>Never let yourself get too busy to go on adventures.
The wind isn’t agreeing with me.//I should head back soon.
Where’s your wetsuit? It’s perfect diving weather…
I’m just here to refill the bird feeder.
Ah, this one still seems to have plenty.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe <NPCName>Suki</> just refilled them.
Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> put me in charge of the town’s decoration and landscaping.//I like doing it, but it’s a lot of work.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I have <NpcName>Pablo</> to help.
Now that I have a lot of free time on my hands, I can finally give back to the community.
Are you stopping by the Tavern?
Today I want to focus on the town’s landscaping.
I don’t mind helping to sort the recyclables.//<portrait=normal>With my children all grown up, it’s nice to feel needed sometimes.
My youngest son, <NpcName>Eddy</>, hasn’t answered my last letter after a week. It’s nothing out of the ordinary for him.//It doesn’t keep me from worrying every time he does it, though.
Good thing <NpcName>Aaliyah</> keeps a close watch on him.//<portrait=concerned>I just wish he would call more often.
I’m not worried about what will happen to Fishensips when I–//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Noah</> are doing great running the Tavern.
Besides, they have <NpcName>Aaliyah</> to help if anything were to go south.//<portrait=happy>I know I can count on my girl to watch over her little siblings.
<NpcName>Frank</> is a joker. I see a lot of my late husband in him.
<NpcName>Noah</> – ah, he’s a sensitive soul. He has a gentle heart, that one.
<NpcName>Connor</> has been mayor for as long as I can remember. He truly cares about Coral Island and the people in it.
Ever since my husband, Frankie, passed away, <NpcName>Frank</> has been stepping up a lot.//I pray for that boy. He has a lot on his shoulders.
That boy has grown to be a very dependable man. His dad would’ve been proud.
The key to baking is to follow the recipe as closely as possible.//Do that, and you’ll get a perfect result 90 percent of the time.
Ten percent of success is down to the quality of the ingredients.
My husband and I used to go diving in the middle of the week.// Afterward, we’d always have big bowls of seafood ramen.
It was our seafood day. I looked forward to it every week.
<NpcName>Emma</> makes terrific food. She’s great with spices.
I’m so proud of her.//<portrait=normal>I still remember when she used to work at Sam’s, and now she has a business of her own.
I wonder if I should wear red to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//It’s a happy day… Thought it might bring some of that same good luck from New Year’s.
Happy New Year, dear… I pray this year is good for you, bringing you a lot of fortune and happiness.
In our house, we never miss eating mooncakes in Fall together…//<portrait=happy>I hope it brings us good luck.
I make sure to always make mooncakes for the Harvest Festival.//It’s good to share them with the people we love.
My children and I used to sit and watch the moon on Fall nights.//<portrait=normal>I’d tell them tales my mother used to tell me. Like stories about the Moon Goddess and her Moon Rabbit.
I like to think Frankie and I did the best we could raising the kids…//<portrait=normal>We might not have had a lot, but we made sure they always got what they needed.
A house needs kids’ laughter, don’t you think?
I try to clean the ceramic plates at least once a year. Get them out of the cabinet, wash them, and put them back.//<portrait=happy>Oh, we don’t use them. Only for the New Year’s dinner, at most.
<NpcName>Aaliyah</> was always a smart kid. Ever since she was a little girl, she got trophies left and right.//Look around, they’re everywhere in this house!
There weren’t a lot of books around when I was a little girl.//<portrait=normal>Now kids have books on their computers and phones.

I used to take the children to visit my parents on New Year’s. Not always, but if we could, we would. This was before, when they were still alive.//It was a good way for the children to spend time with their cousins.//<portrait=concerned>New Year’s visits were important to them…my parents.
You’re a good addition to this community, dear.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.

I used to make my own noodles for birthdays, but now it’s just too much work, especially with four children.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think my hands could take it.//<portrait=normal>Now we just buy noodles to use in my recipes.
I’m trying to make the rounds. I want to make sure the bird feeders are all full before the end of the week.
People around town have been talking about how <NpcName>Frank’s</> cats, Peanut and Butter, go roaming around at night…//I had no idea they were so adventurous.
Oh, you heard that too? Ah, I’m worried about them.//Cats out at night – I don’t think it’s very safe. I wish <NpcName>Frank</> would do something about it.
The stairs are a bit slippery today… I’ll ask <NpcName>Joko</> to take a look. Maybe it’s mold.//Hopefully not. Hopefully, it’s just water or something.
Thinking about how much Fishensips has seen makes me sad sometimes.//We raised four children in it…the cats…Frankie…
It’s good to have a coffee shop in front of Fishensips. It makes the area lively.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Raj</> is a good kid too. They know so much about coffee beans.
We need to restock on oranges. I’ll be taking some to Frankie’s and my parents’ graves soon.//Maybe <NpcName>Noah</> can pick some up from Sam’s.
I watched the twins, <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</>, grow up.//That girl <NpcName>Alice</> was over at the house every other day, playing with my sons, watching TV.
We used to take <NpcName>Alice</> with us to family gatherings. She’s practically family to us.

I was worried when <NpcName>Frank</> was dating that Pokyo girl.//I was afraid he might not want to come back home after university.//<portrait=concerned>With <NpcName>Eddy</> living abroad and <NpcName>Aaliyah</> busy with her duties, I’d be left with just one son to run this place.

If <NpcName>Frank</> had wanted to stay in Pokyo, I guess it would have been fine.//<portrait=sad>Fishensips is big. It’s too much work for one person, but <NpcName>Noah</> could have always hired help.
The water is refreshingly cool today.
The ocean introduced me to a lot of creatures.//<portrait=happy>Keep diving, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m sure it’ll open up to you, too.
Sometimes when we knock on a door, the one who answers it isn’t who we expected…//<portrait=happy>And that’s okay.
Just try to be more patient, dear.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes we forget to be nice to ourselves.
I should make more bird food.//I’m running low.
